        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(queue): restart dormant followup drains",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Restart a dormant follow-up drain when enqueue races with completion of the active reply run.\n- Register the drain against the reply-lane owner so collect-mode batching and queued typing remain intact until lane release.\n- Consolidate session-id adoption for both normal run completion and the race-recovery path.\n\nReimplements the useful idea from #92284 at the reply-run ownership boundary. Thanks @xzh-xydt for the original investigation and test case.\n\nFixes #91909.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm test src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-direct-runtime-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.runreplyagent.e2e.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/queue.collect.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/queue.drain-restart.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/reply-run-registry.test.ts` (152 tests passed)\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.runreplyagent.e2e.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- fresh autoreview: clean\n- Crabbox Azure `run_40cf3f5e6c81` / `cbx_d97ad8f9ba04`: `pnpm check:changed` passed for core and core-tests lanes (typecheck, lint, guards, import cycles)\n\nBehavior addressed: queued follow-up messages no longer remain dormant when enqueue occurs after the active run has already released its queue-drain handoff.\n\nReal environment tested: normal OpenClaw source checkout on macOS with the repository Node/pnpm toolchain.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran the focused auto-reply, E2E, collect-queue, drain-restart, and reply-run-registry test files listed above.\n\nEvidence after fix: the new E2E cases prove immediate drain startup when no reply owner remains and deferred startup when an owner still holds the lane; all 152 focused tests pass.\n\nObserved result after fix: the drain starts exactly after reply-lane release, without starting an admission retry while the original run is active.\n\nWhat was not tested: live channel ingress; the affected queue and reply-lane lifecycle is channel-independent and is covered deterministically at the run/queue boundary.\n",
        "branch": "fix/91909-followup-drain",
